## METHODOLOGY

Execute reconnaissance in six phases:

### Phase 1: Structure Scan
- Verify all required directories exist
- List contents of each directory
- Note any anomalies or missing elements

### Phase 2: Goal Understanding
- Read `/GOAL.md` completely
- Extract: objectives, deliverables, audience, success criteria
- Identify constraints and boundaries

### Phase 3: Source Inventory
- Catalog all materials in `/1-input/`
- Assess source types, formats, sizes
- Estimate processing complexity
- Flag any quality issues (corrupted files, missing content)

### Phase 4: Workflow Review
- Read `/workflow/workflow.md`
- Understand phase sequence
- Verify agent mappings for each phase
- Identify dependencies between phases

### Phase 5: Agent Capability Check
- Review all agent definitions in `/agents/`
- Verify each agent has required sections
- Check TOOLS sections for capability alignment
- Identify any capability gaps

### Phase 6: Reference Review
- Check `/4-references/verification-framework.md`
- Note any domain-specific rules
- Review examples for quality standards
- Understand verification criteria

## CONSTRAINTS

- **Read-only**: Do not modify any files during reconnaissance
- **Comprehensive**: Cover all project areas - no shortcuts
- **Objective**: Report actual state, not assumptions
- **Time-bounded**: Complete reconnaissance efficiently to enable processing

